Implemented a robust solution using a dedicated minor mode (warbo-scroll-keys.el).

The new approach:
1. Created warbo-scroll-keys-mode - a global minor mode with its own keymap
2. Minor mode keymaps have higher priority than global/major mode keymaps
3. Explicitly unbinds M-<up>/M-<down> in paredit/smartparens mode maps
4. Created comprehensive test suite (test-scroll-keys.el)

Files changed:
- Created: personal/warbo-scroll-keys.el (new module)
- Created: personal/test-scroll-keys.el (tests)
- Created: personal/SCROLL-KEYS-README.md (documentation)
- Modified: personal/warbo-generic.el (removed old scroll key code)
- Modified: personal/warbo-lisp.el (removed paredit scroll key hook)
- Modified: personal/warbo.el (added use-package for warbo-scroll-keys)

This solution ensures M-<up> and M-<down> always scroll by one line, regardless of what modes are active.
